        <title>Definition of Digital Literacy</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-4.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-4.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Digital literacy includes a wide range of skills associated with using technology to enable users to find, evaluate, organize, create, and communicate information, including using basic digital skills in meaningful ways. It also means having the skills, strategies, and dispositions to use those skills to solve problems in increasingly technology-rich environments. These skills are important for participation in 21st century life, including education, work, and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="3"&gt;&lt;colgroup&gt;&lt;col width="45%" /&gt;&lt;col width="55%" /&gt;&lt;/colgroup&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;ul style="font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16.0029983520508px;"&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;The term digital literacy means the skills associated with using technology to enable users to find, evaluate, organize, create, and communicate information (U.S. Department of Education, 2015).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul style="font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16.0029983520508px;"&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Digital literacy also means the ability to use those skills to solve problems in the increasingly technology-rich environments of 21st century life (Leu, Kinzer, Coiro, Castek, &amp;amp; Henry, 2013).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/wordle.png" width="233" height="364" alt="Decorative" style="margin: 10px; float: left;" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</contents>
