        <title>Welcome</title>
        <contents>&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-5.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-5.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Welcome to Unit 3! This unit is part of an online module on integrating digital literacy into adult English language instruction. The four units in this professional development module parallel the definition of digital literacy introduced on the previous page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unit 1 focuses on basic digital literacy skills, the importance of digital literacy, and ways to integrate digital literacy meaningfully into instruction. It is a good idea to start with Unit 1 and then move to any of the other units. Unit 2 focuses on information and communication technologies and the ways that creating and communicating information digitally also promotes English language learning. Unit 3 looks at digital information literacy and how to help students learn to find, understand, and critically evaluate information on the Internet. Unit 4 incorporates a wide range of digital literacies into problem-solving in technology-rich environments and is for teachers who have already been integrating digital literacy into their practice and want to take it further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Welcome to Unit 3 of the module on Integrating Digital Literacy Into Adult English Language Instruction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Unit 1: Digital Literacy in Our lives&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Unit 2: Information and Communication Technologies for Language Learning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Unit 3: Digital Information Literacy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Unit 4: Solving Problems in Technology-Rich Environments&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;While this unit can be done on its own, it is best if you first do Unit 1, “Digital Literacy in Our Lives.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;This unit looks at digital information literacy in adult English language instruction. The unit describes how to integrate activities that focus on how to search the Internet, analyze search results, evaluate those results, and read the information critically. A variety of video and web-based resources are included, many of which can be used with students.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
