        <title>Organization of This Unit</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-6.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-6.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This unit is organized so that, first, you focus on yourself and the way that you do (or don’t) use technology to perform a variety of functions in your own life. From this point, the unit presents information about effective Internet searching and ways to help adult English language learners develop skills in Internet searching and evaluating the results by integrating searching activities regularly into your lessons or units. To complete the unit, you will design an activity that you could do in one of your classes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Part 1: Focus on the Teacher&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt; Start-with-what-you-know activity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Part 2: Focus on the Student&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt; An integration approach&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt; SEARCH strategies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt; Exploration activity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Part 3: Internet Search Activity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt; Design an activity to use in your own class&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</contents>
