        <title>Certificate of Completion</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-9.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-9.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You can earn a certificate of completion by doing three activities: completing an activity to think about what you know, completing an exploration activity, and designing an Internet search activity that you could use in your own class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/iStock_000000724284_Small.jpg" width="250" height="187" alt="" style="margin: 5px; float: right;" /&gt;You can earn a certificate of completion by completing the three unit activities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
