        <title>Digital Information Literacy</title>
        <contents>&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-11.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-11.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Using the Internet to find and evaluate information can support English language acquisition and digital literacy development as well as development of a set of soft skills. These soft skills are consistently requested by employers and include, among other things, critical thinking, problem-solving, collaboration skills, and the ability to learn autonomously. These soft skills are particularly important, yet challenging, for adult English language learners because the skills are embedded in cultural assumptions that are likely to be unfamiliar. The soft skills also utilize functional language that needs to be learned, such as making requests and presenting information that may conflict with other’s opinions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Using the Internet to find and evaluate information can support English language learning, digital literacy development, and the  development of skills in  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;critical thinking,   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;problem-solving, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;collaboration, and  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;autonomous learning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="yiv6737391600MsoNormal" id="yui_3_16_0_1_1444861047032_44651"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium; color: #666699;"&gt;&lt;span id="yui_3_16_0_1_1444861047032_44650"&gt;You have reached the end of this lesson.  You may review any of the content in this lesson using the &lt;b&gt;Lesson Menu&lt;/b&gt; on the left of the screen&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="line-height: 1.231;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="yiv6737391600MsoNormal" id="yui_3_16_0_1_1444861047032_44526"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium; color: #666699;"&gt;&lt;span id="yui_3_16_0_1_1444861047032_44525"&gt;If you have finished viewing the lesson, (1) click the &lt;b&gt;NEXT &lt;/b&gt;button on this screen to indicate completion in your progress tracker.  Then, (2) return to the home page to select your next activity.  Activities you have completed will be checked off in your progress tracker&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
