        <title>Employability Skills</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-10.mp3"&gt;ELL_Mod2_U3_Slide-10.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;English language learners preparing for careers, education, and training need to become proficient in information literacy (as show by research by Parrish &amp;amp; Johnson, 2010). More than just language skills for daily life, adult ELLs increasingly need access to things such as information contained in company and training websites that often include cultural and linguistic assumptions unfamiliar to English language learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table border="0" align="right"&gt;&lt;caption&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/skills.png" width="350" height="252" alt="This graphic displays the employability skills framework that includes a central circle titled “Employability.” Surrounding this circle are three categories: Applied knowledge; workplace skills; and effective relationships. On the outside of these categories are specific skills aligned to these categories. For effective relationships this includes: interpersonal skills and personal qualities. For Workplace skills this includes: technology use; systems thinking; communication skills; information use; and resource management. For applied knowledge this includes: resource management; critical thinking skills; and applied academic skills. " style="float: right; margin: 10px;" /&gt;&lt;/caption&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span id="docs-internal-guid-80e343c7-a84e-fb97-b79d-9d55d20b0929"&gt;&lt;a href="http://cte.ed.gov/employabilityskills/index.php/framework/#sthash.p%20P8cPUwr.dpuf" title="Employability Skills Framework" target="_blank"&gt;Employability Skills Framework&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Employability skills are those that are necessary for success in the labor market at all employment levels and in all sectors. See more at  &lt;a href="http://cte.ed.gov/employabilityskills/index.php/framework/#sthash.p%20P8cPUwr.dpuf" title="Employability Skills" target="_blank"&gt;http://cte.ed.gov/employabilityskills/ index.php/framework/#sthash.p P8cPUwr.dpuf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;The ability to find and evaluate information is especially important in work and career settings. All of these skills are identified as highly valuable and necessary by a wide variety of initiatives, including the following:   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.careertech.org/career-clusters" title="Career Clusters Framework" target="_blank"&gt; Career Clusters® Framework&lt;/a&gt;, National Association of State Directors of Career Technical Education Consortium;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.conferenceboard.ca/topics/education/learning-tools/employability-skills.aspx" title="Employability Skills" target="_blank"&gt; Employability Skills 2000+&lt;/a&gt;, The Conference Board of Canada [link]; and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir="ltr"&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://wdr.doleta.gov/SCANS/whatwork/whatwork.pdf" title="Secretary's Commission on Achieving Necessary Skills" target="_blank"&gt; Secretary’s Commission on Achieving Necessary Skills&lt;/a&gt; (SCANS), U.S. Department of Labor [link].&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/68886853_thumbnail.jpg" width="100" height="105" alt="" style="margin: 5px;" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;To Go Deeper&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information about skills that English language learners need for careers, see Preparing English Learners for Work and Career Pathways: Issue Brief, Professional Development Module, and Companion Learning Resource available here: &lt;a href="https://lincs.ed.gov/programs/eslpro" title="LINCS ESL Pro" target="_blank"&gt;https://lincs.ed.gov/programs/eslpro&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
